<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-759-156  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 759 156.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>IEEE Transactions on Robotics and Automation  August 1989 v5 n4p409(9).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Coordinated motion control of multiple robotic devices for weldingand redundancy coordination through constrained operation inCartesian space. (technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ahmad, Shaheen; Luo, Shengwu.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A mathematical algorithm is developed for the coordination of atwo-axis positioning welding table and aseven-axis-degree-of-freedom (a track and a six-axis Cybotech WV15robot manipulator) robot welder.andP;  The strategy involves thepartitioning of the problem into tasks: the welding table alignsthe weld point surface normal 'anti-parallel to gravitydirection,' the robot's weld torch is constrained to the weld pathtrajectory in a down-hand welding position, and robot coordinationachieved through keeping the maneuvering arm far away fromsingular configurations and from the motion limits of the arm andthe tracks.andP;  Redundancy coordination is achieved through ananalytic solution to the problem of optimization ofmaneuverability in Cartesian coordinates.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Robot ArmsManipulatorsNumerical AlgorithmsDynamic ControlOptimization.andO;Feature:   illustrationchartgraph.andO;Caption:   Hierarchical coordination of multiple robotic devices for welding.andO;(chart)Organization of the robot welding system. (chart)World view of weld trajectory. (graph)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>